    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#bazama-jmr1978-1979"/>, p. <citedRange>260</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>37.1714</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>080000</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἁγεμόνα">Ἁγεμόνα</name> <persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἀμμώνιος">Ἀμμωνίου</name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><space quantity="1" unit="character"/> <rs type="office" key="priestess"><w lemma="ἱέρεια">ἱέρεια</w></rs>, <w lemma="χαίρω">χαῖρε</w>.

	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Prêtresse Hagémona fille d'Ammonios, adieu!</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Priestess Hagemona daughter of Ammonios, farewell!</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Sacerdotessa Hagemona figlia di Ammonios, addio!</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>At Ptolemais, the use of koine is usual since the foundation, so that the genitive of the father's name has the expected form. However, the woman's name 
                has the dialectal ending, which was more easily preserved, because in koine feminines in <foreign xml:lang="grc">-a</foreign> do also exist.</p>
	<p>The formula with <foreign xml:lang="grc">χαῖρε</foreign> is never found in Cyrenaica in the Greek period. Ptolemais was more receptive to foreign influences. 
	Besides, this inscription is probably one of the latest in the present collection.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
